history.content:
Are you waitlisted for one of the EE16A labs that are full / do you have enrollment restrictions blocking you from enrolling?

If so, then you can either stay in 61C and wait until Phase 2 for there to be open space for you, and then use the form to get into EE16A (or, at that time, follow the instructions in the next line).

If not, then you should drop 61C, wait until you get into EE16A, and then enroll in 61C. Otherwise, nothing has changed. If you try to enroll in 61C when you're waitlisted for EE16A, then you wouldn't trigger a time conflict form.

children.subject: Update: I dropped myself from the waitlist, enrolled myself in an open lab and discussion section, and was enrolled! Thanks!

I'm glad that you were enrolled, but this is why we ask that you please wait at least a day to fill out our google form. We don't know that you're already enrolled until we look into each and every student's situation.

Yes, I'm waitlisted for the lab which was open at then time that I signed up for the class, but I wasn't automatically enrolled because of reserved seats. But now it's quite full. Do you think it'd be worth it to give up my spot on the waitlist (64) and then try to enroll in an open section? Or would that just leave me somewhere higher up on the waitlist.

history.content:
Hello, I'm currently enrolled in 61C and waitlisted for ee16a. However, my tuesday ee16a lab conflicts with 61C lecture, which is fine since 61C is webcasted. However, I keep getting an email with the subject titled: Enrollment Update: Time conflict. In the email it says that I have a time conflict, and that that I can't get off the waitlist until this conflict is resolved. It tells me to drop the class that I'm enrolled in (61C), and then re enroll and that should trigger the time conflict. However, I've done that twice and have not had a time conflict form show up on my dash board, as I get enrolled back in 61C with no problem. So I filled out the eecs time conflict form for ee16a, and am currently waiting on a response. And today, I received the same email titled Enrollment Update: Time conflict. So I'm not really sure what I'm supposed to to in this situation.  Is there anything else I should be doing to make sure I get into the class?

Thanks
history.subject: Waitlisted for EE16A but keep receiving the same email. Anything else I should be doing.
